@* THE COMPONENT THAT RENDERS ITSELF. Guarded, so Blazor's own renderer TERMINATES on it:
   HtmlRenderer produces <span class="node">x<span class="node">done</span></span>, two levels and
   stop. The guard is a RUNTIME question there -- Blazor instantiates the child, hands it Label,
   and only then evaluates `Label == "x"`.

   Composition here is COMPILE-TIME INLINING (decision 88). The child has no instance, and an @if
   becomes a runtime list() whose body is walked whatever the condition says (decision 81), so the
   walk descends forever. See CycleSelf.razor for what that used to do to the process. *@
<span class="node">@Label@if (Label == "x") { <CycleNode Label="done" /> }</span>

@code {
    [Parameter] public string Label { get; set; } = "";
}
